{{Orphan|date=September 2016}}
'''Anders Petters stuga''' or '''Anders Petters stuga står i ljusan låga''' is an old [[Sweden|Swedish]] [[Christmas music|Christmas song]] of unknown origin. It is often sung when dancing around the [[Christmas tree]]. Alternate lyrics are '''Anders Perssons stuga'''. Lyrical, the song deals with a fire in "Anders Petters'" [[cottage]]. While the lyrics don't mention [[Christmas]], the words "ljusen" are here strongly associated with the [[candle]]s lit at Christmastime.
==Publication== *[[Julens önskesångbok]], 1997, under the lines "Tjugondag Knut dansar julen ut", credited as "folksong"
==Recordings== An early recording was done by [[Margareta Schönström]] in May 1925, and the record came out in 1926.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://smdb.kb.se/catalog/id/002055386|title=Jag minns ; Anders Perssons stuga|publisher=Svensk mediedatabas|language=Swedish|date=1925|accessdate=18 May 2011}}</ref>
